- Stages in communication
    - Speaker
        - Intention
        - Generation
        - Synthesis
    - Hearer
        - Perception
        - Analysis
        - Disambiguation
        - Incorporation
- how can this go wrong
    - S doesnot belive P
    - Speech wreck
    - Ambiguous utterance
- Language Models
    - Coded Language 
        - Speaker has P in mind and codes P in W
        - Header decodes W and reconstructs P
        - P -> W -> W' -> p'
        - P = P' should hold
    - Situated Language 
- Communication through a "Tell and Ask" framework


